                            <comment id="15268944" author="smarsching" created="Tue, 3 May 2016 16:00:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I attached a patch that fixes the problem for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch uses a slightly different approach than outlined in the issue description. Changing AbstractJavadocMojo.createAndResolveArtifact and JavadocPathArtifact seemed to have too much side effects. With my very limited knowledge of the code I cannot guarantee that this would not break anything.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch only modifies AbstractJavadocMojo.getResource and uses the straight-forward way of using the dependency information to resolve a dependency artifact. For fixing the resource loading from dependencies, this patch is sufficient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I still think that createAndResolveArtifact&apos;s behavior of always resolving to the pom.xml is not correct. At least in some places, it is used in a way that does not seem compatible with this behavior. However, my knowledge of the whole plugin code is too limited to understand what the desired outcome would be in these cases (resolving to the referenced project source directory or resolving to the &quot;default&quot; artifact of the referenced project).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that my patch is so simple that it is not protected under any copyright laws, but for practical purposes, I hereby declare that I release it to the public domain.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
